<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-12-11T11:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-12-11T11:00:00-05:00" n="674" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d674">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">033.6511 Grandi, Dino/149: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Chargé in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kirk</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-12-11T11:00:00-05:00">December 11, 1931—11
                                    a.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>161. Your 234<note n="39" xml:id="d674fn39">Not printed.</note> and 235,
                            December 10. I appreciate very much Minister Grandi’s courtesy in giving
                            you in advance an English translation of his speech regarding his visit
                            to the United States. The generous and friendly tone of Signor Grandi’s
                            remarks cannot fail to make a good impression in the United States.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>